    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Widely circulated small, silver French coins introduced in the mid-8th century; appear in debased form until the French Revolution. For comparable English coins, also derived from Roman denarii, use "pennies."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Monedas francesas de plata pequeñas de amplia circulación a mediados del siglo VIII; aparecen en forma degradada hasta la Revolución Francesa. Para monedas inglesas comparables, también derivadas del denario romano, use "penique".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wijdverbreide Franse zilveren muntjes, aangemunt sinds halverwege de 8e eeuw en, met een verlaagd edelmetaalgehalte, gehandhaafd tot de Franse Revolutie. Gebruik 'pennies' voor soortgelijke Engelse munten die eveneens zijn afgeleid van de Romeinse denarii.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>於八世紀中葉推行且廣為流通之法國小型銀幣，法國大革命之前都是以劣質幣的形式出現。自羅馬得納利銀幣演變而來的類似英國硬幣，則稱「便士」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
